About TickTalk

TickTalk is a trusted leader in the kids’ smartwatch industry, delivering safe, reliable, and parent-approved technology for children ages 3–12. Founded in California in 2017, TickTalk was created by parents, for parents—with a mission to help families stay connected in a safer, smarter way.

Over the years, TickTalk has built a strong reputation among families for combining innovative features with advanced parental controls and industry-leading safety standards. Our smartwatches include voice and video calling, real-time GPS tracking, messaging, school mode, SOS, and more—without the risks of internet access or social media.

With thousands of 5-star reviews and a nationwide customer base, TickTalk is the go-to solution for parents looking for a safer phone alternative. Our products are available through Amazon, our official website (myticktalk.com), and growing retail channels. We provide in-house customer service and technical support, ensuring the best possible experience for every family we serve.

About the Role

We are looking for two friendly, detail-oriented Customer Service / Technical Support Representatives to join our growing team. You will be responsible for assisting customers through live chat, phone calls, and emails—handling both pre-sale and post-sale support, troubleshooting issues, and ensuring every customer has a positive experience with our products.

This role also includes supporting TickTalk Wireless customers with:

SIM card activation
Subscription plan setup and billing questions
Monthly usage checks and account management assistance
Key Responsibilities

Respond to customer inquiries via live chat, phone, and email
Resolve frequently asked questions and common troubleshooting scenarios
Guide customers through product setup and app usage
Support customers with TickTalk Wireless activation and subscription-related questions
Assist with both pre-purchase product questions and post-purchase support
Accurately log tickets, customer information, and issue resolutions
Escalate complex cases to internal teams when necessary
Ensure timely follow-ups and maintain high customer satisfaction
Qualifications

Previous experience in customer service, technical support, or consumer electronics preferred
Familiarity with Zendesk or other ticketing/CRM systems is a strong plus
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Strong troubleshooting skills and a problem-solving mindset
Ability to multitask, prioritize, and work independently or in a team
Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook)
Bilingual (Spanish/English) is a plus
High school diploma or equivalent required
Passion for working with families and making tech support simple and friendly
What We Offer

Paid training and onboarding support
A collaborative and mission-driven team
Bonus opportunities based on performance and company goals
Opportunities to grow as the company expands
A chance to make a difference in the lives of families and children
