Company Overview:

CompliancyIT is a fast-growing IT Services, Security, and Compliance Company with primary operations out of Greensburg, PA and Front Royal, VA. At CIT, we empower businesses with secure, compliant, and high-performing IT environments. Through strategic infrastructure services and compliance-focused support, we help our clients meet evolving regulatory requirements (CMMC, ISO 27001, NIST 800-171) while achieving their business objectives. As we grow and integrate newly acquired teams, we are committed to excellence, agility, and continuous improvement.

Our Massive Transformative Purpose is to create an environment where awesome people join to do meaningful work to grow personally and professionally and to believe in themselves. Our meaningful work is assessing, securing, maintaining, and configuring IT infrastructure, cloud platforms, servers, and computers. We use our guiding Principles to make decisions and determine what action to take. We are a tight knit team with high visibility and accountability. We specialize in providing CMMC Compliance services for businesses in the Defense Industrial Base.

Our 3 Non-Negotiables are: Security is Paramount, Detailed Documentation, Excellence in Communication.

And we align to our 5 company Principles:

Trust in Radical Truth and Radical Transparency
CIT is the Team and the Clients
Get and Stay Aligned
Learn, Test, Iterate.
Manage the Organization Through Systems and Processes
We are scaling up - so if you thrive in a fast-moving environment where you work with high performers, read on...

Mission of the Position:

The mission of the Junior Systems Engineer is to support the design, implementation, and operation of secure, stable, and compliant infrastructure under the guidance of senior engineers, while developing the technical judgment and systems thinking required for long-term ownership.

Junior Systems Engineers contribute to infrastructure projects and ongoing system improvements by executing well-defined engineering tasks, validating configurations, and producing accurate documentation (network diagrams, updating baseline configuration templates to current state, creating/updating Standard Operating Procedures).

They are expected to learn how individual components interact across servers (on premises and virtual), identity (Entra, AD), networking (on premises and virtual), and cloud services (primarily M365 commercial and GCCH), and to understand how infrastructure decisions impact security, compliance, and operational resilience.

Operating across multiple client environments, Junior Systems Engineers build confidence by following standards, asking good questions, and learning from complexity, gradually moving from task execution toward broader system responsibility while upholding CompliancyIT’s commitment to security, documentation, and excellence in communication.

Key Criteria/Requirements:

2–4 years of experience in IT systems administration, infrastructure support, or a technical escalation role (Service Desk Level 2/3, Jr. Engineer, or equivalent)
U.S. Based, U.S. Citizen
Hands-on experience supporting and configuring servers, cloud platforms, or networked environments under the guidance of senior engineers
Prior exposure to working in multi-client or MSP environments
Experience deploying infrastructure projects or migrations
Foundational Technical Competencies:

Servers & Server Operating Systems

Working knowledge of:
- Windows Server fundamentals (Active Directory, DNS, Group Policy)
- Server patching, backups, and basic hardening practices
- Ability to execute defined configuration changes accurately and safely

Microsoft 365 / Azure / Entra

Practical experience administering or supporting:
- Microsoft 365 tenants
- Entra ID (Azure AD) users, security groups, MFA, and access controls

Familiarity with:
- Exchange Online, SharePoint, OneDrive
- Intune or device management concepts

Ability to follow identity and security standards without deviation
Networking Fundamentals

Solid understanding of:
- TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, and basic routing concepts
- Firewall rules, VPNs, and secure remote access (conceptual and operational)

Ability to troubleshoot common connectivity and name-resolution issues
Execution, Discipline & Reliability

Ability to:
- Follow documented standards, procedures, and change processes
- Execute tasks with accuracy and attention to detail
- Validate work and confirm outcomes before handoff

Strong time management and task prioritization skills in a structured environment
Documentation & Communication

Clear written documentation skills:
- Accurate technical change notes
- Updating baseline configurations post-change
- Creating and updating network diagrams

Ability to communicate:
- Status, blockers, and questions clearly to senior engineers and project manager
- Technical information concisely and professionally

Learning Mindset & Coachability

Demonstrated curiosity and willingness to learn
Comfortable asking questions and accepting feedback
Ability to apply lessons learned and improve execution over time
Desire to grow into broader system ownership and engineering responsibility
Security & Compliance Awareness

Demonstrated security-conscious mindset:
- Understands why security controls and safeguards exist, not just how to configure them
- Follows least privilege and change management discipline

Familiarity with compliance frameworks such as NIST CSF and NIST 800-171/CMMC.
Willingness to learn how infrastructure supports compliance and audit readiness
Operational Expectations

Comfortable working across multiple client environments
Willingness to support incident response activities under guidance
Strong alignment with CompliancyIT’s:
- Non-Negotiables (Security is Paramount, Detailed Documentation, Excellence in Communication)
- The Principles (core values) which stress a culture of accountability, integrity, and continuous improvement

